\label{09.05.2023--1} We summarily present basic results on dilatations of rings following the more general path given in \cite{Ma23d}. Let $A$ be a ring. A {\it center in $A$} is a pair $[M,a]$ consisting of an ideal $M\subset A$ and an element $a\in A$. A {\it multi-center} is a family of center indexed by some set. Let $I$ be an index set and let $\{[M_i , a_i] \}_{i \in I}$ be a multi-center. For $i \in I$, we put $L_i = M_i +(a_i)$, an ideal of $A$. Let $ bN _I $ be the monoid $ igoplus _{i \in I}  bN $. If $
u = (
u_1 , \ldots , 
u_i, \ldots ) \in  bN _I $ we put $L^{
u}= L_1 ^{
u_1} \cdots L_i ^{
u _i} \cdots $ (product of ideals of $A$) and $a^{
u}= a_1^{
u_1 } \cdots a_i ^{
u _i} \cdots$ (product of elements of $A$). We also put $a^{ bN _I} = \{ a^
u | 
u \in  bN _I \}$. \depr[{\cite{Ma23d}}] \label{generaldila} The dilatation of $A$ with multi-center $\{[M_i , a_i] \}_{i \in I}$ is the unital commutative ring $A[ ig\{  rac{M_i}{a_i} ig\}_{i \in I}]$ defined as follows: $ ullet$ The underlying set of $A[ ig\{  rac{M_i}{a_i} ig\}_{i \in I}]$ is the set of equivalence classes of symbols $ rac{m}{a^{
u}} $ where $ 
u \in  bN _I$ and $m \in L^{
